President Trump addressed a gathering of governors at the White House, expressing his appreciation for their presence and their previous experiences as governors. He emphasized the need for states to be the "laboratories of democracy" and spoke about the importance of reducing federal government regulations. Trump also discussed his upcoming budget, which will focus on public safety, national security, and defense spending. He mentioned his plans to repeal and replace Obamacare, and his intention to restore local control to the education system. Trump concluded by expressing his desire to work with the governors on various projects and invited them to share their opinions and ask questions.